.. table:: RS232 / RS485 / CAN Pin Definition for 10.1 inch and above products
   :align: center
   :width: 100%
   :class: align-center
   :widths: auto

   +----------------+-------------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------+
   | **Pin Number** | **Definition**                | **Description**                                              | OS Node                |
   +================+===============================+==============================================================+========================+
   | Pin 1          | CAN_H                         | CPU SPI0, CAN H signal                                       |                        |
   +----------------+-------------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------+
   | Pin 2          | CAN_L                         | CPU SPI0, CAN L signal                                       | CAN0                   |
   +----------------+-------------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------+
   | Pin 3          | RS485_5-                      | CPU UART5, RS485 –(B) signal                                 |                        |
   +----------------+-------------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------+
   | Pin 4          | RS485_5+                      | CPU UART5, RS485 +(A) signal                                 | /dev/ttyAMA4           |
   +----------------+-------------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------+
   | Pin 5          | RS485_3-                      | CPU UART3, RS485 –(B) signal                                 |                        |
   +----------------+-------------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------+
   | Pin 6          | RS485_3+                      | CPU UART3, RS485 +(A) signal                                 | /dev/ttyAMA2           |
   +----------------+-------------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------+
   | Pin 7          | RS232_2_RXD                   | CPU UART2, RS232 RXD signal                                  |                        |
   +----------------+-------------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------+
   | Pin 8          | RS232_2_TXD                   | CPU UART2, RS232 TXD signal                                  | /dev/ttyAMA1           |
   +----------------+-------------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------+
   | Pin 9          | RS232_0_RXD                   | CPU UART0, RS232 RXD signal, Debug Port                      |                        |
   +----------------+-------------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------+
   | Pin 10         | RS232_0_TXD                   | CPU UART0, RS232 TXD signal  Debug Port                      | /dev/ttyAMA0           |
   +----------------+-------------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------+
   | Pin 11         | GND                           | System Ground                                                |                        |
   +----------------+-------------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------+
   | Pin 12         | +5V                           | System +5V Power Output, No more than 1A Current output      |                        |
   +----------------+-------------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------+

:pagebreak:`True`
